31.07	The_Man_Who_Shot_Liberty_Valance	The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance	The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance is a 1962 American Western film directed by John Ford and starring James Stewart and John Wayne. The black-and-white film was released by Paramount Pictures. The screenplay by James Warner Bellah and Willis Goldbeck was adapted from a short story written by Dorothy M. Johnson.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/b/b7/The_Man_Who_Shot_Liberty_Valance.jpg/220px-The_Man_Who_Shot_Liberty_Valance.jpg
